				\begin{document}$$i^\text {th}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M12"><mml:msup><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mtext>th</mml:mtext></mml:msup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2022_4779_Article_IEq6.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> subpopulation present in the system. Subpopulations here represent the cells bearing the same set of driver mutations (see below), i.e., cancer clones, Accordingly, all cells belonging to the same subpopulation will have the same state. Note that, by design, subpopulation <inline-formula id="IEq7"><alternatives><tex-math id="M13">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
